apers", "Washington (D.C.)", "United States--District of Columbia--Washington"], "subjects": [{"district of columbia": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:district+of+columbia&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}, {"washington": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:washington&fo=json"}, {"washington (d.c.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:washington+%28d.c.%29&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2022-10-24T21:21:29.352Z", "title": "Evening star (Washington, D.C.), January 23, 1938", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045462/1938-01-23/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83045462/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn83045462", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/9a682579-45b6-5780-a200-302fe01da28d"], "batch": ["dlc_englishsetter_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1854", "description": ["Daily, Mar. 26, 1905-July 12, 1972 Vol. 4, no. 553 (Oct. 9, 1854)-120th year, no. 194 (July 12, 1972). \"From April 25 through May 24, 1861 one sheet issues were published intermittently owing to scarcity of paper.\" Cf. Library of Congress, Photoduplication Service. Publisher varies: Noyes, Baker & Co., <1867>; Evening Star Newspaper Co., <1868-> Suspended Jan. 1-6, 1971 because of a machinists' strike. Archived issues are available in digital format as part of the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Also issued on microfilm from Microfilming Corp. of America and the Library of Congress, Photoduplication Service. Washington daily news (Washington, D.C.) (DLC)sn 82016181 (OCoLC)9186073 Evening star and the Washington daily news (DLC)sn 83045463 (OCoLC)9567065"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:12.885Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-01", "catalog", "u